      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No worries about the goblin! As for the faucet, you'll want to turn off the water at the main valve to prevent any unexpected geysers when you wrestle with the handle. If there's a shutoff under the sink, that's a great backup, but just in case, the main valve is your trusty shield against water chaos. To remove the handle without stripping the screw, gently wiggle it back and forth while turning counterclockwise. If it resists, you can apply a bit of penetrating oil and let it sit for a few minutes. The trick is to be patient and gentle, like coaxing a shy goblin to reveal its treasures. Once the handle is loose, you can twist it off and dive into the depths of your faucet's inner workings. Good luck!",
